-- NHL Is Preparing to Hold Six Outdoor Games Next Season, TSN Says
-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 2013-04-17T18:00:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-17/nhl-is-preparing-to-hold-six-outdoor-games-next-season-tsn-says.html
The National Hockey League is
preparing to hold six outdoor games next season including the
Winter Classic planned for New Yearâ€™s Day between the  Toronto
Maple Leafs  and  Detroit Red Wings  at Michigan Stadium, TSN in
Canada reported.  The games, subject to contracts being completed, will be
held after the annual Jan. 1 Winter Classic, TSN said on its
 website .  The Anaheim Ducks and Los Angeles Kings would play at
Dodger Stadium on Jan. 25; the  New York Rangers  would face the
New York Islanders and New Jersey Devils in separate games on
Jan. 26 and Jan. 29 at Yankee Stadium; the Pittsburgh Penguins
would take on the Chicago Blackhawks at Soldier Field on March
1; and the Ottawa Senators would play the Vancouver Canucks at
B.C. Place Stadium on March 2, TSN said. The games in New York
would be the week before the Super Bowl, which is Feb. 2 at
MetLife Stadium in East Rutherford, New Jersey.  To contact the reporter on this story:
